  "correctAnswer": 2,
  "explanation": [
    "Conservation of momentum: <katex>$p_{\\alpha} = p_{recoil}$</katex>.",
    "Kinetic Energy <katex>$K = p^2/2m$</katex>, so <katex>$K \\propto 1/m$</katex>.",
    "<katex>$\\frac{K_{\\alpha}}{K_{recoil}} = \\frac{m_{recoil}}{m_{\\alpha}} = \\frac{220-4}{4} = \\frac{216}{4} = 54$</katex>.",
    "<katex>$K_{\\alpha} = \\frac{m_{recoil}}{m_{total}} Q$</katex> (approx formula). Actually <katex>$K_{\\alpha} = \\frac{A-4}{A} Q$</katex>.",
    "<katex>$K_{\\alpha} = \\frac{216}{220} \\times 5.5 = \\frac{54}{55} \\times 5.5 = 5.4 MeV$</katex>."
